{"title_page": "Deep Green Resistance", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{POV|date=March 2013}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2014}}}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name   = Deep Green Resistance\n| logo   = Deep Green Resistance.jpg\n| founded_date      = 2011\n| founder           = [[Derrick Jensen]], [[Lierre Keith]], Aric McBay\n| location          = USA\n| focus             = [[Environmental justice]], [[Social justice]]\n| method            = [[Direct action]], education\n| homepage          = {{URL|deepgreenresistance.org}}\n}}\n\n'''Deep Green Resistance''' ('''DGR''') is a radical [[environmental movement]] that views mainstream [[Environmentalism|environmental activism]] as being ineffective. The group believes that [[industrial civilization]], as they define it, is endangering the environment, and that must be destroyed using a broad range of tactics including [[militancy]].<ref name=McBay>McBay, Aric, Lierre Keith, and Derrick Jensen. 2011. ''Deep Green Resistance.'' New York: Seven Stories Press.</ref>\n\n==Beliefs==\nIn the 2011 book ''Deep Green Resistance'', the authors [[Lierre Keith]], [[Derrick Jensen]] and Aric McBay state that civilization, particularly [[industrialisation|industrial civilization]], is fundamentally [[unsustainable]] and must be actively and urgently dismantled in order to secure a future for all species on the planet.<ref name=McBay/> Civilization is defined as agriculture and cities. DGR argues that industry is unsustainable, [[Environmental impact of agriculture|agriculture is detrimental]] and cities surpass the natural [[carrying capacity]] of the land.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nThe term was created for a 2007 conference entitled ''Deep Green Resistance. Confronting Industrial Culture'' in [[Deerfield, Massachusetts]]. Keith was the main organizer.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nLike [[Earth First!]], DGR's principles stem from the concept of [[deep ecology]] and state that all species are inherently equal, and thus humans are not superior to any other form of life.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nDGR holds [[bright green environmentalism]] to be inadequate. DGR believes that lifestyle changes, such as using travel mugs and reusable bags and taking shorter showers, are too small for the large-scale environmental problems the world faces. It also states that the recent surge in environmentalism has become commercial in nature, and thus in itself has been industrialized. The movement asserts that per person the industrial waste produced is orders of magnitude greater than the home waste produced; therefore, it is industrialism that must be ended, and with that, lifestyle changes will follow.<ref name=McBay/>\n\nCritics point out that DGR does not offer a feasible method for accelerating the massive numbers of human deaths predicted,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.therightplanet.com/2012/01/deep-green-resistance-occupy-until-it-all-falls-apart/ |title=Deep Green Resistance: Occupy Until It All Falls Apart |website=Therightplanet.com |date=2012-01-02 |accessdate=2016-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804020325/http://www.therightplanet.com/2012/01/deep-green-resistance-occupy-until-it-all-falls-apart/ |archive-date=2016-08-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref> but Keith and Jensen contend that while the reality of them not being actually able to slaughter millions of people is unpleasant, an [[apocalypse]] is inevitable anyway and delaying [[mass murder]] will only result in more suffering and that they are merely trying to prepare the world for the forthcoming death and wide-scale violence. Jensen states that if activists do not wish to participate in [[terrorism]] and [[murder]], they, at the very least, should prepare to set up local committees to reduce or channel the additional violence.<ref>{{cite web|title=It's Time to Get Out|author=Jensen, Derrick|work=Endgame|url=http://www.endgamethebook.org/Excerpts/18-Time-Get-Out.html}}</ref>\n\nBesides Keith, Jensen is a member of the advisory board.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nThe DGR claims to be [[radical feminist]].<ref name=radfem>{{cite web |url= http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/faq-radical-feminism/ |title=FAQ: Radical Feminism |work=deepgreenresistance.org |year=2013 |accessdate=5 June 2013}}</ref> DGR has been described as [[transphobic]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://earthfirstnews.wordpress.com/2013/05/15/deep-green-transphobia/ |title=Deep Green Transphobia |work=earthfirstnews.wordpress.com |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> A [[Transitioning (transgender)|transitioning]] member, identifying as a woman, requested to join a women's communal sleeping and showering space and, later, a women's caucus space; this was refused.<ref name=\"radfem\"/> McBay claimed he \"left the organization at the beginning of 2012 after a trans inclusive policy was cancelled by Jensen and Keith. Many ... people ... left the organization for that reason\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.aricmcbay.org/2013/05/14/dgr-and-transphobia/ |title=DGR and Transphobia |first=Aric |last=McBay |work=aricmcbay.org |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/2013/05/16/deep-green-reclamation/ |title=Deep Green Resignation and Reclamation &#124; Earth First! Newswire |website=Earthfirstjournal.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://conference.resistanceecology.org/ |title=Resistance Ecology Comes To An&nbsp;End |website=Conference.resistanceecology.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227025016/https://conference.resistanceecology.org/ |archive-date=2013-12-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> A 2013 post on the DGR website quixotically titled ''Protect Women, Feminism, and Free Speech'' protests and defines gender as non-existent.<ref name=\"deepgreenresistance.org\">{{cite web |url= http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/protect-women-feminism-and-free-speech/ |title=Protect Women, Feminism, and Free Speech |work=deepgreenresistance.org |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> DGR views gender as a brutal and corrupt caste system that requires destruction.<ref name=\"radfem\"/>\n\n==Tactics==\nConsidering that the majority of global society will not voluntary starve or die, the DGR believes armed warfare is necessary. It dismisses that any gradual shift to [[sustainability]] is possible. DGR believes that industrial civilization will inevitably collapse, that they must act decisively before the collapse to ensure that the Earth remains inhabitable for all organisms, and build a more sustainable society after the collapse. DGR supports an active resistance movement with the objective of accelerating the collapse of industrial civilization.<ref name=McBay/> Jensen has concluded that \"the mass of civilized people will never be on our side.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LGL8PCVc_pcC&pg=PT173&lpg=PT173&dq=%22The+mass+of+civilized+people+will+never+be+on+our+side%22+jensen&source=bl&ots=crnwS2f7R7&sig=Pg8F6ze5TXizSQ23qnKw3wpSaFg&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yxCNUdzXOIi5rgH89YDgAw&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAQ |title=The Derrick Jensen Reader: Writings on Environmental Revolution |author=Derrick Jensen |website=Books.google.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> This has led to organizing a strategy that is pessimistic about popular involvement, and therefore aims at forcing change without the majority's consensus.<ref name=Taylor2013>{{cite web|last=Taylor |first=Bron |url=http://www.earthisland.org/journal/index.php/elist/eListRead/resistance_do_the_ends_justify_the_means |title=Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means? &#124; Latest News &#124; Earth Island Journal &#124; Earth Island Institute |website=Earthisland.org |date=2013-04-26 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\nDGR holds that lifestyle change is not effective. Mainstream environmentalism is criticised for its emphasis on individual lifestyle changes and technological solutions, instead of confronting and holding individuals, industries, institutions and society accountable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orionmagazine.org/index.php/articles/article/4801/ |title=Forget Shorter Showers |publisher=Orion Magazine |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fertileground1.ning.com/page/a-context-for-fg |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 6, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009210832/http://fertileground1.ning.com/page/a-context-for-fg |archivedate=October 9, 2009 }}</ref> The founders of the DGR view technological solutions, no matter how well-intentioned, as unsatisfactory and warn that they could even lead to accelerated environmental destruction.<ref name=McBay/>\n\nIn the organization's [[eponymous]] book, Keith lists a number of reasons where she finds violence justified, although she understands that people \"who care about justice want to reject violence\".<ref name=McBay/> Keith and McBay have openly encouraged a clandestine militant network, and DGR provides support for such action.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deepgreenresistance.org|title=Deep Green Resistance Homepage|website=Deepgreenresistance.org|accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\nThe organisation supports [[war]] and [[militancy]] in order to achieve its goals.<ref name=DGRDEW>{{cite web|title=Decisive Ecological Warfare|url=http://deepgreenresistance.org/en/deep-green-resistance-strategy/decisive-ecological-warfare|website=deepgreenresistance.org|publisher=Deep Green Resistance|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> The foundational book of the DGR details how a network of \"well-organized underground militants\" are to rise up in \"coordinated attacks\" to obliterate industrial infrastructure \"perhaps using electromagnetic pulses\".<ref name=C&C>{{cite web|author=Ian Angus|title='Deep Green Resistance' \u2013 How not to build a movement - A path to certain defeat |url=http://climateandcapitalism.com/2012/05/10/deep-green-resistance-a-path-to-certain-defeat/|website=climateandcapitalism.com|publisher=Climate & Capitalism|format=Book review|date=May 10, 2012 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> The DGR describes militant action as a potentially necessary means to achieve the drastic changes they desire. The DGR endorses violent strategies for [[social action]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.counterpunch.org/2011/12/20/deep-green-resistance/ |title=Deep Green Resistance |website=Counterpunch.org |date=2011-12-20 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> In a YouTube video they posted McBay and Keith promote the idea of clandestine networks organized along hierarchical lines, with frontline troops disciplined by a command structure,<ref>{{cite video|title=Deep Green Resistance - Strategy to Save the Planet|publisher=YouTube|date=12 August 2011|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9ZxBg1CbmG8}}</ref> and hierarchies are best for organizing an [[insurgency]].<ref name=McBay/>\n\nJensen predicts that in the future the authorities will try to arrest members. He dismisses mass [[genocide]] as acceptable considering \"global economy is murdering humans and non-humans\" and \"don't blame those who want to stop ... exploitation... help to stop the exploitation\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Millions Killed?|work=Deep Green Resistance|url=http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/faq/millionskilled/|accessdate=February 2013}}</ref> He has clarified such ideas on ''[[Democracy Now!]]'': \"I get accused of being the 'violence guy' ... I want to put everything on the table ... it's appropriate to have militant response or non-militant response.\"<ref name = DN112610>{{cite interview|last=Jensen|first=Derrick|interviewer=[[Amy Goodman]]|work=[[Democracy Now!]]|date=26 November 2010|url=http://www.democracynow.org/2010/11/26/author_and_activist_derrick_jensen|title=Author and Activist Derrick Jensen: \"The Dominant Culture is Killing the Planet...It\u2019s Very Important for Us to Start to Build a Culture of Resistance\"}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism==\nIn '''Deep Green Resistance' \u2013 How not to build a movement - A path to certain defeat'', a 2012 review of the 2011 DGR manifesto, Ian Angus criticizes DGR's ideas as polarizing, elitist, extremist or asocial.<ref name=C&C/> Regarding advocacy for [[dictatorship]], [[eco-terrorism]] and [[genocide]] Bron Taylor argues in ''Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means?'' that \"radical tactics tend to be counterproductive\" in winning the general public.<ref name=Taylor2013>{{cite web|last=Taylor |first=Bron |url=http://www.earthisland.org/journal/index.php/elist/eListRead/resistance_do_the_ends_justify_the_means |title=Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means? &#124; Latest News &#124; Earth Island Journal &#124; Earth Island Institute |website=Earthisland.org |date=2013-04-26 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\n[[Anarcho-primitivist]]s [[John Zerzan]], [[Kevin Tucker (anarchist)|Kevin Tucker]] and others criticise the promotion of hierarchy in organising militants, the code of conduct, the historical understanding of revolution and radical history, and the [[cult of personality]] around Jensen and Keith.<ref name=\"sproutdistro1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sproutdistro.com/2013/05/18/deep-green-resistance-a-book-review/ |title=Deep Green Resistance: A Book Review |publisher=Sprout Distro |date=2013-05-18 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref name=\"EF Critique\">{{cite web|url=http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/articles/deep-green-resistance-a-critique|title=Deep Green Resistance \u2014 a critique|first1=Michelle|last1=Matisons|first2=Alexander Reid|last2=Ross|publisher=[[Earth First!]] Journal|year=2014\u20132015|access-date=2015-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140803103416/http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/articles/deep-green-resistance-a-critique/|archive-date=2014-08-03|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=Zerzan>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/AnarchyRadio03-08-2011/ |title=Anarchy Radio 03-08-2011 : John Zerzan : Free Download & Streaming : Internet Archive |website=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://enkidu.anarchyplanet.org/2011/06/10/authority-and-civilization/ |title=Authority and civilization |accessdate=May 21, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120710101150/http://enkidu.anarchyplanet.org/2011/06/10/authority-and-civilization/ |archivedate=July 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt might also be mentioned that genocide and [[terrorism]] are illegal; and advocating them because of [[millenarian]] delusions is [[misanthropic]] and [[sociopathic]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Deep ecology]]\n*[[Eco-terrorism]]\n*[[Luddite]]\n*[[Radical environmentalism]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n\n[[Category:Environmental organizations based in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deep ecology]]\n[[Category:Radical environmentalism]]\n[[Category:Simple living]]\n[[Category:Anti-consumerist groups]]\n[[Category:Anti-capitalism]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{POV|date=March 2013}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2014}}}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name   = Deep Green Resistance\n| logo   = Deep Green Resistance.jpg\n| founded_date      = 2011\n| founder           = [[Derrick Jensen]], [[Lierre Keith]], Aric McBay\n| location          = USA\n| focus             = [[Environmental justice]], [[Social justice]]\n| method            = [[Direct action]], education\n| homepage          = {{URL|deepgreenresistance.org}}\n}}\n\n'''Deep Green Resistance''' ('''DGR''') is a radical [[environmental movement]] that views mainstream [[Environmentalism|environmental activism]] as being ineffective. The group believes that [[industrial civilization]], as they define it, is endangering the environment, and that must be destroyed using a broad range of tactics including [[militancy]].<ref name=McBay>McBay, Aric, Lierre Keith, and Derrick Jensen. 2011. ''Deep Green Resistance.'' New York: Seven Stories Press.</ref>\n\n==Beliefs==\nIn the 2011 book ''Deep Green Resistance'', the authors [[Lierre Keith]], [[Derrick Jensen]] and Aric McBay state that civilization, particularly [[industrialisation|industrial civilization]], is fundamentally [[unsustainable]] and must be actively and urgently dismantled in order to secure a future for all species on the planet.<ref name=McBay/> Civilization is defined as agriculture and cities. DGR argues that industry is unsustainable, [[Environmental impact of agriculture|agriculture is detrimental]] and cities surpass the natural [[carrying capacity]] of the land.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nThe term was created for a 2007 conference entitled ''Deep Green Resistance. Confronting Industrial Culture'' in in [[Deerfield, Massachusetts]]. Keith was the main organizer.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nLike [[Earth First!]], DGR's principles stem from the concept of [[deep ecology]] and state that all species are inherently equal, and thus humans are not superior to any other form of life.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nDGR holds [[bright green environmentalism]] to be inadequate. DGR believes that lifestyle changes, such as using travel mugs and reusable bags and taking shorter showers, are too small for the large-scale environmental problems the world faces. It also states that the recent surge in environmentalism has become commercial in nature, and thus in itself has been industrialized. The movement asserts that per person the industrial waste produced is orders of magnitude greater than the home waste produced; therefore, it is industrialism that must be ended, and with that, lifestyle changes will follow.<ref name=McBay/>\n\nCritics point out that DGR does not offer a feasible method for accelerating the massive numbers of human deaths predicted,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.therightplanet.com/2012/01/deep-green-resistance-occupy-until-it-all-falls-apart/ |title=Deep Green Resistance: Occupy Until It All Falls Apart |website=Therightplanet.com |date=2012-01-02 |accessdate=2016-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804020325/http://www.therightplanet.com/2012/01/deep-green-resistance-occupy-until-it-all-falls-apart/ |archive-date=2016-08-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref> but Keith and Jensen contend that while the reality of them not being actually able to slaughter millions of people is unpleasant, an [[apocalypse]] is inevitable anyway and delaying [[mass murder]] will only result in more suffering and that they are merely trying to prepare the world for the forthcoming death and wide-scale violence. Jensen states that if activists do not wish to participate in [[terrorism]] and [[murder]], they, at the very least, should prepare to set up local committees to reduce or channel the additional violence.<ref>{{cite web|title=It's Time to Get Out|author=Jensen, Derrick|work=Endgame|url=http://www.endgamethebook.org/Excerpts/18-Time-Get-Out.html}}</ref>\n\nBesides Keith, Jensen is a member of the advisory board.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nThe DGR claims to be [[radical feminist]].<ref name=radfem>{{cite web |url= http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/faq-radical-feminism/ |title=FAQ: Radical Feminism |work=deepgreenresistance.org |year=2013 |accessdate=5 June 2013}}</ref> DGR has been described as [[transphobic]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://earthfirstnews.wordpress.com/2013/05/15/deep-green-transphobia/ |title=Deep Green Transphobia |work=earthfirstnews.wordpress.com |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> A [[Transitioning (transgender)|transitioning]] member, identifying as a woman, requested to join a women's communal sleeping and showering space and, later, a women's caucus space; this was refused.<ref name=\"radfem\"/> McBay claimed he \"left the organization at the beginning of 2012 after a trans inclusive policy was cancelled by Jensen and Keith. Many ... people ... left the organization for that reason\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.aricmcbay.org/2013/05/14/dgr-and-transphobia/ |title=DGR and Transphobia |first=Aric |last=McBay |work=aricmcbay.org |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/2013/05/16/deep-green-reclamation/ |title=Deep Green Resignation and Reclamation &#124; Earth First! Newswire |website=Earthfirstjournal.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://conference.resistanceecology.org/ |title=Resistance Ecology Comes To An&nbsp;End |website=Conference.resistanceecology.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227025016/https://conference.resistanceecology.org/ |archive-date=2013-12-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref> A 2013 post on the DGR website quixotically titled ''Protect Women, Feminism, and Free Speech'' protests and defines gender as non-existent.<ref name=\"deepgreenresistance.org\">{{cite web |url= http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/protect-women-feminism-and-free-speech/ |title=Protect Women, Feminism, and Free Speech |work=deepgreenresistance.org |year=2013 |accessdate=19 May 2013}}</ref> DGR views gender as a brutal and corrupt caste system that requires destruction.<ref name=\"radfem\"/>\n\n==Tactics==\nConsidering that the majority of global society will not voluntary starve or die, the DGR believes armed warfare is necessary. It dismisses that any gradual shift to [[sustainability]] is possible. DGR believes that industrial civilization will inevitably collapse, that they must act decisively before the collapse to ensure that the Earth remains inhabitable for all organisms, and build a more sustainable society after the collapse. DGR supports an active resistance movement with the objective of accelerating the collapse of industrial civilization.<ref name=McBay/> Jensen has concluded that \"the mass of civilized people will never be on our side.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LGL8PCVc_pcC&pg=PT173&lpg=PT173&dq=%22The+mass+of+civilized+people+will+never+be+on+our+side%22+jensen&source=bl&ots=crnwS2f7R7&sig=Pg8F6ze5TXizSQ23qnKw3wpSaFg&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yxCNUdzXOIi5rgH89YDgAw&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAQ |title=The Derrick Jensen Reader: Writings on Environmental Revolution |author=Derrick Jensen |website=Books.google.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> This has led to organizing a strategy that is pessimistic about popular involvement, and therefore aims at forcing change without the majority's consensus.<ref name=Taylor2013>{{cite web|last=Taylor |first=Bron |url=http://www.earthisland.org/journal/index.php/elist/eListRead/resistance_do_the_ends_justify_the_means |title=Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means? &#124; Latest News &#124; Earth Island Journal &#124; Earth Island Institute |website=Earthisland.org |date=2013-04-26 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\nDGR holds that lifestyle change is not effective. Mainstream environmentalism is criticised for its emphasis on individual lifestyle changes and technological solutions, instead of confronting and holding individuals, industries, institutions and society accountable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orionmagazine.org/index.php/articles/article/4801/ |title=Forget Shorter Showers |publisher=Orion Magazine |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fertileground1.ning.com/page/a-context-for-fg |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 6, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009210832/http://fertileground1.ning.com/page/a-context-for-fg |archivedate=October 9, 2009 }}</ref> The founders of the DGR view technological solutions, no matter how well-intentioned, as unsatisfactory and warn that they could even lead to accelerated environmental destruction.<ref name=McBay/>\n\nIn the organization's [[eponymous]] book, Keith lists a number of reasons where she finds violence justified, although she understands that people \"who care about justice want to reject violence\".<ref name=McBay/> Keith and McBay have openly encouraged a clandestine militant network, and DGR provides support for such action.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deepgreenresistance.org|title=Deep Green Resistance Homepage|website=Deepgreenresistance.org|accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\nThe organisation supports [[war]] and [[militancy]] in order to achieve its goals.<ref name=DGRDEW>{{cite web|title=Decisive Ecological Warfare|url=http://deepgreenresistance.org/en/deep-green-resistance-strategy/decisive-ecological-warfare|website=deepgreenresistance.org|publisher=Deep Green Resistance|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> The foundational book of the DGR details how a network of \"well-organized underground militants\" are to rise up in \"coordinated attacks\" to obliterate industrial infrastructure \"perhaps using electromagnetic pulses\".<ref name=C&C>{{cite web|author=Ian Angus|title='Deep Green Resistance' \u2013 How not to build a movement - A path to certain defeat |url=http://climateandcapitalism.com/2012/05/10/deep-green-resistance-a-path-to-certain-defeat/|website=climateandcapitalism.com|publisher=Climate & Capitalism|format=Book review|date=May 10, 2012 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> The DGR describes militant action as a potentially necessary means to achieve the drastic changes they desire. The DGR endorses violent strategies for [[social action]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.counterpunch.org/2011/12/20/deep-green-resistance/ |title=Deep Green Resistance |website=Counterpunch.org |date=2011-12-20 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref> In a YouTube video they posted McBay and Keith promote the idea of clandestine networks organized along hierarchical lines, with frontline troops disciplined by a command structure,<ref>{{cite video|title=Deep Green Resistance - Strategy to Save the Planet|publisher=YouTube|date=12 August 2011|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9ZxBg1CbmG8}}</ref> and hierarchies are best for organizing an [[insurgency]].<ref name=McBay/>\n\nJensen predicts that in the future the authorities will try to arrest members. He dismisses mass [[genocide]] as acceptable considering \"global economy is murdering humans and non-humans\" and \"don't blame those who want to stop ... exploitation... help to stop the exploitation\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Millions Killed?|work=Deep Green Resistance|url=http://www.deepgreenresistance.org/faq/millionskilled/|accessdate=February 2013}}</ref> He has clarified such ideas on ''[[Democracy Now!]]'': \"I get accused of being the 'violence guy' ... I want to put everything on the table ... it's appropriate to have militant response or non-militant response.\"<ref name = DN112610>{{cite interview|last=Jensen|first=Derrick|interviewer=[[Amy Goodman]]|work=[[Democracy Now!]]|date=26 November 2010|url=http://www.democracynow.org/2010/11/26/author_and_activist_derrick_jensen|title=Author and Activist Derrick Jensen: \"The Dominant Culture is Killing the Planet...It\u2019s Very Important for Us to Start to Build a Culture of Resistance\"}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism==\nIn '''Deep Green Resistance' \u2013 How not to build a movement - A path to certain defeat'', a 2012 review of the 2011 DGR manifesto, Ian Angus criticizes DGR's ideas as polarizing, elitist, extremist or asocial.<ref name=C&C/> Regarding advocacy for [[dictatorship]], [[eco-terrorism]] and [[genocide]] Bron Taylor argues in ''Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means?'' that \"radical tactics tend to be counterproductive\" in winning the general public.<ref name=Taylor2013>{{cite web|last=Taylor |first=Bron |url=http://www.earthisland.org/journal/index.php/elist/eListRead/resistance_do_the_ends_justify_the_means |title=Resistance: Do the Ends Justify the Means? &#124; Latest News &#124; Earth Island Journal &#124; Earth Island Institute |website=Earthisland.org |date=2013-04-26 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\n[[Anarcho-primitivist]]s [[John Zerzan]], [[Kevin Tucker (anarchist)|Kevin Tucker]] and others criticise the promotion of hierarchy in organising militants, the code of conduct, the historical understanding of revolution and radical history, and the [[cult of personality]] around Jensen and Keith.<ref name=\"sproutdistro1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sproutdistro.com/2013/05/18/deep-green-resistance-a-book-review/ |title=Deep Green Resistance: A Book Review |publisher=Sprout Distro |date=2013-05-18 |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref name=\"EF Critique\">{{cite web|url=http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/articles/deep-green-resistance-a-critique|title=Deep Green Resistance \u2014 a critique|first1=Michelle|last1=Matisons|first2=Alexander Reid|last2=Ross|publisher=[[Earth First!]] Journal|year=2014\u20132015|access-date=2015-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140803103416/http://earthfirstjournal.org/newswire/articles/deep-green-resistance-a-critique/|archive-date=2014-08-03|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=Zerzan>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/AnarchyRadio03-08-2011/ |title=Anarchy Radio 03-08-2011 : John Zerzan : Free Download & Streaming : Internet Archive |website=Archive.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://enkidu.anarchyplanet.org/2011/06/10/authority-and-civilization/ |title=Authority and civilization |accessdate=May 21, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120710101150/http://enkidu.anarchyplanet.org/2011/06/10/authority-and-civilization/ |archivedate=July 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt might also be mentioned that genocide and [[terrorism]] are illegal; and advocating them because of [[millenarian]] delusions is [[misanthropic]] and [[sociopathic]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Deep ecology]]\n*[[Eco-terrorism]]\n*[[Luddite]]\n*[[Radical environmentalism]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n\n[[Category:Environmental organizations based in the United States]]\n[[Category:Deep ecology]]\n[[Category:Radical environmentalism]]\n[[Category:Simple living]]\n[[Category:Anti-consumerist groups]]\n[[Category:Anti-capitalism]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_Green_Resistance"}
{"title_page": "Sambavar", "text_new": "[[Tamil Sambavar]]\n", "text_old": "[[Adi Andhra]]\n", "name_user": "Wiseinfo07", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sambavar"}
{"title_page": "Bailey Gate railway station", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox UK disused station\n | name = Bailey Gate\n | gridref = SY949995\n | image_name = Bailey Gate Station - geograph.org.uk - 1741936.jpg\n | caption = Bailey Gate railway station in April 1963\n | original = [[Dorset Central Railway]]\n | pregroup = [[Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway]]\n | postgroup = {{ubl|Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway|[[Southern Region of British Railways]]}}\n | locale = [[Sturminster Marshall]]\n | borough = [[East Dorset]]\n | platforms = 2\n | years = 1 November 1860\n | events = Opened (Sturminster Marshall)\n | years1 = 31 August 1863\n | events1 = Renamed (Bailey Gate)\n | years2 = 7 March 1966\n | events2 = Closed\n}}\n\n'''Bailey Gate railway station''' was on the [[Somerset & Dorset Joint Railway]] in the [[England|English]] county of [[Dorset]].\n\nThe station served the [[United Dairies]] cheese factory and the village of [[Sturminster Marshall]] but was named after a local farm to avoid confusion with another station on the same railway at [[Sturminster Newton]]. \n\nThe station had extensive sidings and was one of the largest depots for transporting milk on the UK railway system. Milk was carried in [[British Railway Milk Tank Wagon|tanker wagons]] from Bailey Gate to London and was a major source of revenue for the railway. [[Sugar beet]] was also loaded onto wagons for transportation to refineries. \n\nThe station consisted of three buildings, a Waiting Room/Ticket Office, a small shed for the lamps on the downside and a signalbox on the upside, behind the station were the sidings for transhipment. Access to the station from the west was via a small path that ran down from the slope of the bridge, which took the user to the up platform where, to gain access to the station buildings, one had to cross the railway lines via a small wooden crossing next to the bridge. Access from the east was via the main entrance to the goods sidings down the slope and around the side of the station via a gateway.  The station closed with the railway under the [[Beeching Axe]] in March 1966. Track was finally lifted in 1969, as the railway remained open until the closure of the goods terminal at [[Blandford Forum railway station|Blandford]] that year.\n\nThere is now an industrial estate off the [[A350 road]] called \"Bailie Gate\" at the site.\n\n==References== \n{{Reflist}}\n* {{Butt-Stations}}\n* {{Jowett-Nationalised}}\n* {{Jowett-Atlas}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.npemap.org.uk/tiles/map.html#394,99,1 Station on navigable O.S. map]\n\n{{Disused Rail Start}}\n{{rail line two to one |previous1=[[Corfe Mullen railway station|Corfe Mullen]]<br><small>Line and station closed</small> |previous2={{stnlnk|Wimborne}}<br /><small>Line and station closed</small> |next=[[Spetisbury railway station|Spetisbury]]<br><small>Line and station closed</small>|route=[[Somerset & Dorset Joint Railway]]<br><small>[[London and South Western Railway|LSWR]] & [[Midland Railway]]s</small> |col={{SDJR colour}} }}\n{{end box}}\n\n{{coord|50.79504|-2.07373|type:railwaystation_region:GB_source:enwiki-osgb36(SY949995)|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Disused railway stations in Dorset]]\n[[Category:Former Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1860]]\n[[Category:Railway stations closed in 1966]]\n[[Category:Beeching closures in England]]\n\n{{SouthWestEngland-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox UK disused station\n | name = Bailey Gate\n | gridref = SY949995\n | image_name = Bailey Gate Station - geograph.org.uk - 1741936.jpg\n | caption = Bailey Gate railway station in April 1963\n | original = [[Dorset Central Railway]]\n | pregroup = [[Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway]]\n | postgroup = {{ubl|Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway|[[Southern Region of British Railways]]}}\n | locale = [[Sturminster Marshall]]\n | borough = [[East Dorset]]\n | platforms = 2\n | years = 1 November 1860\n | events = Opened (Sturminster Marshall)\n | years1 = 31 August 1863\n | events1 = Renamed (Bailey Gate)\n | years2 = 7 March 1966\n | events2 = Closed\n}}\n\n'''Bailey Gate railway station''' was on the [[Somerset & Dorset Joint Railway]] in the [[England|English]] county of [[Dorset]].\n\nThe station served the [[United Dairies]] Cheese Factory and the village of [[Sturminster Marshall]] but was named after a local farm to avoid confusion with another station on the same railway at [[Sturminster Newton]]. \n\nThe station had extensive sidings and was one of the largest depots for transporting milk on the UK railway system. Milk was carried in [[British Railway Milk Tank Wagon|tanker wagons]] from Bailey Gate to London and was a major source of revenue for the railway. [[Sugar Beet]] was also loaded onto wagons for transportation to refineries. \n\nThe station consisted of three buildings, a Waiting Room/Ticket Office, a small shed for the lamps on the downside and a signalbox on the upside, behind the station were the sidings for transhipment. Access to the station from the west was via a small path that ran down from the slope of the bridge, which took the user to the up platform where, to gain access to the station buildings, one had to cross the railway lines via a small wooden crossing next to the bridge. Access from the east was via the main entrance to the goods sidings down the slope and around the side of the station via a gateway.  The station closed with the railway under the [[Beeching Axe]] in March 1966. Track was finally lifted in 1969, as the railway remained open until the closure of the goods terminal at [[Blandford Forum railway station|Blandford]] that year.\n\nThere is now an industrial estate off the [[A350 road]] called \"Bailie Gate\" at the site.\n\n==References== \n{{Reflist}}\n* {{Butt-Stations}}\n* {{Jowett-Nationalised}}\n* {{Jowett-Atlas}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.npemap.org.uk/tiles/map.html#394,99,1 Station on navigable O.S. map]\n\n{{Disused Rail Start}}\n{{rail line two to one |previous1=[[Corfe Mullen railway station|Corfe Mullen]]<br><small>Line and station closed</small> |previous2={{stnlnk|Wimborne}}<br /><small>Line and station closed</small> |next=[[Spetisbury railway station|Spetisbury]]<br><small>Line and station closed</small>|route=[[Somerset & Dorset Joint Railway]]<br><small>[[London and South Western Railway|LSWR]] & [[Midland Railway]]s</small> |col={{SDJR colour}} }}\n{{end box}}\n\n{{coord|50.79504|-2.07373|type:railwaystation_region:GB_source:enwiki-osgb36(SY949995)|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Disused railway stations in Dorset]]\n[[Category:Former Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1860]]\n[[Category:Railway stations closed in 1966]]\n[[Category:Beeching closures in England]]\n\n{{SouthWestEngland-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "David Biddulph", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:capitalisation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bailey_Gate_railway_station"}
{"title_page": "The Age of Surveillance Capitalism", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n\n'''''The Age of Surveillance Capitalism''''' is a 2018 non-fiction book by Professor [[Shoshana Zuboff]] which looks at the development of digital companies like Google and Amazon, and suggests that their business models represent a new form of capitalist accumulation that she calls \"[[surveillance capitalism]]\".<ref>{{cite news|first1=James|last1=Bridle|accessdate=2020-01-17|title=The Age of Surveillance Capitalism by Shoshana Zuboff review \u2013 we are the pawns|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/feb/02/age-of-surveillance-capitalism-shoshana-zuboff-review|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2 February 2019|issn=0261-3077|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first1=John|last1=Naughton|accessdate=2020-01-17|title='The goal is to automate us': welcome to the age of surveillance capitalism|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jan/20/shoshana-zuboff-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-google-facebook|newspaper=The Observer|date=20 January 2019|issn=0029-7712|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nZuboff states that [[Surveillance capitalism|Surveillance Capitalism]] \"unilaterally claims human experience as free raw material for translation into behavioural data [which] are declared as a proprietary ''behavioural surplus'', fed into advanced manufacturing processes known as \u2018machine intelligence\u2019, and fabricated into ''prediction products'' that anticipate what you will do now, soon, and later.\" She states that these new capitalist products \"are traded in a new kind of marketplace that I call ''behavioural futures markets''.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jan/20/shoshana-zuboff-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-google-facebook|title='The goal is to automate us': welcome to the age of surveillance capitalism|last=Naughton|first=John|date=2019-01-20|work=The Observer|access-date=2020-01-16|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\nIn a capitalist society, information, such as a users likes and dislikes, observed from accessing a platform like [[facebook]] is information that can be freely used by that platform to better the experience of a user by feeding them information that data obtained from their previous activity would have shown them to be interested in. This in many ways can be done through the use of an [[algorithm]] that automatically filters out information. The danger of surveillance capitalism is that platforms and tech companies are entitled to this information because it is free for them to access. There is very little supervision by governments and users themselves. Because of this, there has been backlash on how these companies have used the information gathered. For example, [[Google]], which is said to be \u201cthe pioneer of [[surveillance capitalism]]\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":023\">{{Cite journal|last=Zuboff|first=Shoshana|last2=M\u00f6llers|first2=Norma|last3=Murakami Wood|first3=David|last4=Lyon|first4=David|date=2019-03-31|title=Surveillance Capitalism: An Interview with Shoshana Zuboff|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|journal=Surveillance & Society|volume=17|issue=1/2|pages=257\u2013266|doi=10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|issn=1477-7487}}</ref> introduced a feature that used \u201ccommercial models\u2026discovered by people in a time and place\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":023\" />. This means that not only are commercials being specifically targeted to you through your phone, but now work hand in hand with your environment and habits such as being shown an advertisement of a local bar when walking around downtown in the evening. Advertising attempts this technical and specific can easily have an impact on the one's decision-making process in the activities they choose and in political decisions. Thus the idea that these companies seemingly go unchecked whilst having the power to observe and control thinking is one of the many reasons tech companies such as Google themselves are under so much scrutiny. \n\nFurthermore, the freedom allotted to tech companies comes from the idea that \u201csurveillance capitalism does not abandon established capitalist \u2018laws\u2019 such as competitive production, [[profit maximization]], productivity and growth\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":033\">{{Cite journal|last=Zuboff|first=Shoshana|last2=M\u00f6llers|first2=Norma|last3=Murakami Wood|first3=David|last4=Lyon|first4=David|date=2019-03-31|title=Surveillance Capitalism: An Interview with Shoshana Zuboff|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|journal=Surveillance & Society|volume=17|issue=1/2|pages=257\u2013266|doi=10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|issn=1477-7487}}</ref>, as they are principles any business in a capitalistic society should aim to excel in, in order to be competitive. Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":033\" /> claims in an article that \u201cnew logic accumulation\u2026introduces its own laws of motion\u201d. In other words, this is a new phenomenon in capitalistic operations that should be treated as such and be instilled with its own specific restrictions and limitations. Lastly, as invasive as platforms have been in terms of accumulating information, they have also led to what is now called a \u201c[[sharing economy]]\u201d, Van Dijck (2018)<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite journal|last=van Dijck|first=Jos\u00e9|last2=Poell|first2=Thomas|last3=de Waal|first3=Martijn|date=2018-10-18|title=The Platform Society|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/oso/9780190889760.001.0001|journal=Oxford Scholarship Online|doi=10.1093/oso/9780190889760.001.0001}}</ref> in which digital information can be obtained by individuals carrying out their own surveillance capitalism through the aid of platforms themselves. Thus \u201cindividuals can greatly benefit from this transformation because it empowers them to set up business\u201d, Van Dijck (2018)<ref name=\":14\" />. Small businesses will also benefit in potentially growing faster than they would have without knowing consumer demands and wants. This leaves surveillance capitalism as an exceptionally useful tool for businesses, but also an invasion of privacy to users. \n\n<br />\n==Reception==\n''The New Yorker'' listed ''The Age of Surveillance Capitalism'' as one of its top non-fiction books of 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/2019-in-review/our-favorite-nonfiction-books-of-2019|title=Our Favorite Nonfiction Books of 2019|last=Yorker|first=The New|date=2019-12-18|access-date=2020-01-16|language=en|issn=0028-792X}}</ref> Barack Obama also listed it as one of his favourite books of 2019, which journalism researcher Avi Asher-Schapiro noted as an interesting choice, given that the book heavily criticises the \"revolving door of personnel who migrated between Google & the Obama admin\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mashable.com/article/obama-favorites-2019-the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism/|title=Obama praises book that slams his White House for its Google relationship|last=Binder|first=Matt|website=Mashable|language=en|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref>\n\nSam DiBella, writing for the ''LSE Blog,'' criticised the book's approach which could \"inspire paralysis rather than praxis when it comes to forging collective action to counter systematic corporate surveillance.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.lse.ac.uk/usappblog/2019/11/10/book-review-the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-the-fight-for-a-human-future-at-the-new-frontier-of-power-by-shoshana-zuboff/|title=Book Review: The Age of Surveillance Capitalism: The Fight for a Human Future at the New Frontier of Power by Shoshana Zuboff|last=November 10th|last2=Reviews|first2=2019{{!}}Book|date=2019-11-10|website=USAPP|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-16|last3=Democracy|last4=Comments|first4=culture{{!}}0}}</ref>\n\n''The Financial Times'' called the book a \"masterwork of original thinking and research\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ig.ft.com/sites/business-book-award/books/2019/shortlist/the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-by-shoshana-zuboff/|title=The Age of Surveillance Capitalism by Shoshana Zuboff|last=Graphics|first=FT Interactive|website=FT Business book of the year award|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Age of Surveillance Capitalism, The}}\n[[Category:American non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:2018 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Books critical of capitalism]]\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}\n\n'''''The Age of Surveillance Capitalism''''' is a 2018 non-fiction book by Professor [[Shoshana Zuboff]] which looks at the development of digital companies like Google and Amazon, and suggests that their business models represent a new form of capitalist accumulation that she calls \"[[surveillance capitalism]]\".<ref>{{cite news|first1=James|last1=Bridle|accessdate=2020-01-17|title=The Age of Surveillance Capitalism by Shoshana Zuboff review \u2013 we are the pawns|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2019/feb/02/age-of-surveillance-capitalism-shoshana-zuboff-review|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2 February 2019|issn=0261-3077|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first1=John|last1=Naughton|accessdate=2020-01-17|title='The goal is to automate us': welcome to the age of surveillance capitalism|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jan/20/shoshana-zuboff-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-google-facebook|newspaper=The Observer|date=20 January 2019|issn=0029-7712|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nZuboff states that [[Surveillance capitalism|Surveillance Capitalism]] \"unilaterally claims human experience as free raw material for translation into behavioural data [which] are declared as a proprietary ''behavioural surplus'', fed into advanced manufacturing processes known as \u2018machine intelligence\u2019, and fabricated into ''prediction products'' that anticipate what you will do now, soon, and later.\" She states that these new capitalist products \"are traded in a new kind of marketplace that I call ''behavioural futures markets''.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/jan/20/shoshana-zuboff-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-google-facebook|title='The goal is to automate us': welcome to the age of surveillance capitalism|last=Naughton|first=John|date=2019-01-20|work=The Observer|access-date=2020-01-16|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\nIn a capitalist society, information, such as a users likes and dislikes, observed from accessing a platform like [[facebook]] is information that can be freely used by that platform to better the experience of a user by feeding them information that data obtained from their previous activity would have shown them to be interested in. This in many ways can be done through the use of an [[algorithm]] that automatically filters out information. The danger of surveillance capitalism is that platforms and tech companies are entitled to this information because it is free for them to access. There is very little supervision by governments and users themselves. Because of this, there has been backlash on how these companies have used the information gathered. For example, [[Google]], which is said to be \u201cthe pioneer of [[surveillance capitalism]]\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":023\">{{Cite journal|last=Zuboff|first=Shoshana|last2=M\u00f6llers|first2=Norma|last3=Murakami Wood|first3=David|last4=Lyon|first4=David|date=2019-03-31|title=Surveillance Capitalism: An Interview with Shoshana Zuboff|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|journal=Surveillance & Society|volume=17|issue=1/2|pages=257\u2013266|doi=10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|issn=1477-7487}}</ref> introduced a feature that used \u201ccommercial models\u2026discovered by people in a time and place\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":023\" />. This means that not only are commercials being specifically targeted to you through your phone, but now work hand in hand with your environment and habits such as being shown an advertisement of a local bar when walking around downtown in the evening. Advertising attempts this technical and specific can easily have an impact on the one's decision-making process in the activities they choose and in political decisions. Thus the idea that these companies seemingly go unchecked whilst having the power to observe and control thinking is one of the many reasons tech companies such as Google themselves are under so much scrutiny. \n\nFurthermore, the freedom allotted to tech companies comes from the idea that \u201csurveillance capitalism does not abandon established capitalist \u2018laws\u2019 such as competitive production, [[profit maximization]], productivity and growth\u201d, Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":033\">{{Cite journal|last=Zuboff|first=Shoshana|last2=M\u00f6llers|first2=Norma|last3=Murakami Wood|first3=David|last4=Lyon|first4=David|date=2019-03-31|title=Surveillance Capitalism: An Interview with Shoshana Zuboff|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|journal=Surveillance & Society|volume=17|issue=1/2|pages=257\u2013266|doi=10.24908/ss.v17i1/2.13238|issn=1477-7487}}</ref>, as they are principles any business in a capitalistic society should aim to excel in in order to be competitive. Zuboff (2019)<ref name=\":033\" /> claims in an article that \u201cnew logic accumulation\u2026introduces its own laws of motion\u201d. In other words, this is a new phenomenon in capitalistic operations that should be treated as such and be instilled with its own specific restrictions and limitations. Lastly, as invasive as platforms have been in terms of accumulating information, they have also led to what is now called a \u201c[[sharing economy]]\u201d, Van Dijck (2018)<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite journal|last=van Dijck|first=Jos\u00e9|last2=Poell|first2=Thomas|last3=de Waal|first3=Martijn|date=2018-10-18|title=The Platform Society|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/oso/9780190889760.001.0001|journal=Oxford Scholarship Online|doi=10.1093/oso/9780190889760.001.0001}}</ref> in which digital information can be obtained by individuals carrying out their own surveillance capitalism through the aid of platforms themselves. Thus \u201cindividuals can greatly benefit from this transformation because it empowers them to set up business\u201d, Van Dijck (2018)<ref name=\":14\" />. Small businesses will also benefit in potentially growing faster than they would have without knowing consumer demands and wants. This leaves surveillance capitalism as an exceptionally useful tool for businesses, but also an invasion of privacy to users. \n\n<br />\n==Reception==\n''The New Yorker'' listed ''The Age of Surveillance Capitalism'' as one of its top non-fiction books of 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/2019-in-review/our-favorite-nonfiction-books-of-2019|title=Our Favorite Nonfiction Books of 2019|last=Yorker|first=The New|date=2019-12-18|access-date=2020-01-16|language=en|issn=0028-792X}}</ref> Barack Obama also listed it as one of his favourite books of 2019, which journalism researcher Avi Asher-Schapiro noted as an interesting choice, given that the book heavily criticises the \"revolving door of personnel who migrated between Google & the Obama admin\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mashable.com/article/obama-favorites-2019-the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism/|title=Obama praises book that slams his White House for its Google relationship|last=Binder|first=Matt|website=Mashable|language=en|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref>\n\nSam DiBella, writing for the ''LSE Blog,'' criticised the book's approach which could \"inspire paralysis rather than praxis when it comes to forging collective action to counter systematic corporate surveillance.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.lse.ac.uk/usappblog/2019/11/10/book-review-the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-the-fight-for-a-human-future-at-the-new-frontier-of-power-by-shoshana-zuboff/|title=Book Review: The Age of Surveillance Capitalism: The Fight for a Human Future at the New Frontier of Power by Shoshana Zuboff|last=November 10th|last2=Reviews|first2=2019{{!}}Book|date=2019-11-10|website=USAPP|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-16|last3=Democracy|last4=Comments|first4=culture{{!}}0}}</ref>\n\n''The Financial Times'' called the book a \"masterwork of original thinking and research\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ig.ft.com/sites/business-book-award/books/2019/shortlist/the-age-of-surveillance-capitalism-by-shoshana-zuboff/|title=The Age of Surveillance Capitalism by Shoshana Zuboff|last=Graphics|first=FT Interactive|website=FT Business book of the year award|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Age of Surveillance Capitalism, The}}\n[[Category:American non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:2018 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Books critical of capitalism]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "comma", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Age_of_Surveillance_Capitalism"}
{"title_page": "Anolis eewi", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n{{speciesbox\n| name      = ''Anolis eewi''\n| genus     = Anolis\n| species   = eewi\n| authority = [[Janis Roze|Roze]], 1958\n}}\n\n'''''Anolis eewi''''', commonly known as the '''goldenscale anole''', is a [[species]] of the [[lizard]] in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Dactyloidae]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://reptile-database.reptarium.cz/species?genus=Anolis&species=planiceps|title=Anolis planiceps|work=The Reptile Database|access-date=2018-01-02}}</ref>\n\n==Geographic range==\n''Anolis eewi'' is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Bolivar, Venezuela|Bolivar]], [[Venezuela]].<ref name=\":0\" /> It may be found on the [[Chimant\u00e1 Massif|Chimant\u00e1]] [[Tepui]].\n\n==Etymology==\nThe [[Specific name (zoology)|specific name]], ''eewi'', is in honor of [[Americans|American]] [[Herpetology|herpetologist]] [[:fr:Ernest Edward Williams|Ernest E. Williams]], a wordplay on his initials, E.E.W.<ref>Beolens, Bo; Watkins, Michael; Grayson, Michael (2011). ''The Eponym Dictionary of Reptiles''. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. xiii + 296 pp. {{ISBN|978-1-4214-0135-5}}. (''Anolis eewi'', p. 81).</ref>\n\n==Original publication==\n*[[Janis Roze|Roze J]] (1958). \"''Los reptiles del Chimant\u00e1 Tepui (Estado Bol\u00edvar, Venezuela) colectados por la expedici\u00f3n bot\u00e1nica del'' Chicago Natural History Museum\". ''Acta Biol\u00f3gica Venezuelica'' '''2''' (25): 299-314. (''Anolis eewi'', new species, p.&nbsp;311). (in Spanish).\neoeer\n[eorr\neeie\neoiwee\nuwueyw\neiueeyeete\nieueyeweueyr\nieeuyryerr\nreruruyr\nrpe;repr;erurr\neieyeeweuee\n[[File:Eee7e|thumb|eeueyeerue]]\neoeelerorebccbcc\neuw8e8ee6e9e\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2814334}}\n\n[[Category:Anoles|E]]\n[[Category:Lizards of South America]]\n[[Category:Endemic fauna of Venezuela]]\n[[Category:Reptiles of Venezuela]]\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}\n{{speciesbox\n| name      = ''Anolis eewi''\n| genus     = Anolis\n| species   = eewi\n| authority = [[Janis Roze|Roze]], 1958\n}}\n\n'''''Anolis eewi''''', commonly known as the '''goldenscale anole''', is a [[species]] of the [[lizard]] in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Dactyloidae]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://reptile-database.reptarium.cz/species?genus=Anolis&species=planiceps|title=Anolis planiceps|work=The Reptile Database|access-date=2018-01-02}}</ref>\n\n==Geographic range==\n''Anolis eewi'' is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Bolivar, Venezuela|Bolivar]], [[Venezuela]].<ref name=\":0\" /> It may be found on the [[Chimant\u00e1 Massif|Chimant\u00e1]] [[Tepui]].\n\n==Etymology==\nThe [[Specific name (zoology)|specific name]], ''eewi'', is in honor of [[Americans|American]] [[Herpetology|herpetologist]] [[:fr:Ernest Edward Williams|Ernest E. Williams]], a wordplay on his initials, E.E.W.<ref>Beolens, Bo; Watkins, Michael; Grayson, Michael (2011). ''The Eponym Dictionary of Reptiles''. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. xiii + 296 pp. {{ISBN|978-1-4214-0135-5}}. (''Anolis eewi'', p. 81).</ref>\n\n==Original publication==\n*[[Janis Roze|Roze J]] (1958). \"''Los reptiles del Chimant\u00e1 Tepui (Estado Bol\u00edvar, Venezuela) colectados por la expedici\u00f3n bot\u00e1nica del'' Chicago Natural History Museum\". ''Acta Biol\u00f3gica Venezuelica'' '''2''' (25): 299-314. (''Anolis eewi'', new species, p.&nbsp;311). (in Spanish).\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2814334}}\n\n[[Category:Anoles|E]]\n[[Category:Lizards of South America]]\n[[Category:Endemic fauna of Venezuela]]\n[[Category:Reptiles of Venezuela]]\n", "name_user": "49.145.7.26", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eOriginal publicaertion)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anolis_eewi"}
{"title_page": "Tony Zosherafatain", "text_new": "'''Tony Zosherafatain''' (born December 21, 1987) is an American [[Film director|director]], producer, and [[writer]] from [[Boston|Boston, Massachusetts]]. He openly identifies as a [[transgender]] man and has directed and produced award-winning films about trans identity. As a documentarian, his films utilize a character-driven lens to portray [[Transidentity|trans identity]], [[intersectionality]], [[civil and political rights]], and [[political movements]]. He is the current [[Film director|Director]] of ''[https://www.transintrumpland.com/ Trans in Trumpland,]'' a forthcoming documentary about the [[Trump (president)|Trump]] administration's impact on transgender [[Americans]]. The film is produced through [https://www.transwavefilms.com TransWave Films], a production company run by Zosherafatain and fellow trans filmmaker Jamie DiNicola, and is supported by Executive Producer [[Miss Major Griffin-Gracy]]. [[Jason B. Kohl]] serves as Lead Editor of ''Trans in Trumpland'' alongside [[Tchavdar Georgiev]] as Consulting Editor. After a successful [[Kickstarter]] campaign<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/transintrumpland/trans-in-trumpland/description|title=Trans in Trumpland Kickstarter|last=|first=|date=|website=Kickstarter|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and media coverage by [[GLAAD]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glaad.org/blog/glaad-wrap-trailers-now-apocalypse-and-billions-critics-choice-award-winners-and-more|title=The GLAAD Wrap: Trailers for 'Now Apocalypse' and 'Billions,' Critics' Choice Award winners, and more!|date=2019-01-17|website=GLAAD|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, the film completed production in 2019 and is in post-production.<ref>{{Citation|title=Trans in Trumpland|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt9163946/|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nTony began his film career in 2012 after realizing that there weren't many films about transgender stories.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm8697282/|title=Tony Zosherafatain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> His current and prior films include ''[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt12079070/?ref_=nm_knf_t1 Finding Cedar,] [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11056716/?ref_=nm_knf_t4 Fratello], [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6407488/?ref_=nm_knf_t3 I am Isak,] and [https://www.transwavefilms.com/venture-out Venture Out]''. Venture Out was selected for distribution by [[Recreational Equipment, Inc.|REI]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rei.com/blog/hike/rei-presents-venture-out|title=REI Presents: Venture Out|last=Staff|first=R. E. I.|date=2020-02-20|website=REI Co-op Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His films have screened at domestic and international [[Film festival|film festivals,]] including [[Inside Out Film and Video Festival|Inside Out]], [https://www.theemerginglens.com Emerging Lens], Thessaloniki LGBT Film Festival<ref>{{Citation|title=I am Isak|url=https://www.filmfestival.gr/en/movie/movie/7546|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, and [[Shanghai Queer Film Festival]]. He was the recipient of a Finalist Award at Emerging Lens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theemerginglens.com/awards|title=2017 AWARD WINNERS...|website=emerginglens|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nHis writing blends his identity background, personal anecdotes, and commentary on societal issues to reflect on modern [[American society]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Nixon|first=Paul G.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NR0xDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT109&lpg=PT109&dq=tony+zosherafatain+writer&source=bl&ots=qaYbEi2c1m&sig=ACfU3U1sWpkoRaeFCvVAF6WIilPXZR7wpg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj1sMalpu7oAhVUhHIEHSLxAog4ChDoATABegQICxAo#v=onepage&q=tony%20zosherafatain%20writer&f=false|title=Sex in the Digital Age|last2=D\u00fcsterh\u00f6ft|first2=Isabel K.|date=2017-08-16|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-315-44622-6|language=en}}</ref> He began writing for the [[HuffPost|Huffington Post]] in 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/author/anthony-zosherafatain|title=Tony Zosherafatain {{!}} HuffPost|website=www.huffpost.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> after realizing he faced unique challenges as a transgender [[Iranian Americans|Iranian-American.]] After releasing an article entitled \"I\u2019m Iranian-American. This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like\", his writing was published on the [[HuffPost|Huffington Post]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/im-iranian-american-this-is-what-trumps-america_b_58a49fb3e4b0cd37efcfefd5|title=I'm Iranian-American. This Is What Trump's America Feels Like.|last=Zosherafatain|first=Tony|last2=filmmaker|first2=ContributorI'm a|date=2017-02-15|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16|last3=Writer|first3=A.|last4=Immigrants|first4=The Son of|last5=Person|first5=A. Progress-Minded}}</ref>, [[Thought Catalog]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/tony-zosherafatain/2017/03/im-iranian-american-and-this-is-what-trumps-america-feels-like-to-me/|title=I\u2019m Iranian-American And This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like To Me|date=2017-03-28|website=Thought Catalog|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and [[Medium (website)|Medium.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.politicsmeanspolitics.com/im-iranian-american-this-is-what-trump-s-america-feels-like-7345e666b6b8|title=I\u2019m Iranian-American. This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like.|last=Zosherafatain|first=Tony|date=2017-02-20|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> He appeared in [[Mark Seliger]]'s book ''[https://www.rizzoliusa.com/book/9780847858316/ On Christopher Street: Transgender Stories]'' and was featured in the [[The New York Times|New York Times]]<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bernstein|first=Jacob|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/29/style/transgender-christopher-street-photography-book-mark-seliger.html|title=A Trans Life, Captured by Mark Seliger|date=2016-09-28|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and [[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate (LGBT magazine).]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/books/2016/10/04/transgender-stories-christopher-street-photos|title=Transgender Stories on Christopher Street (Photos)|date=2016-10-04|website=www.advocate.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> In 2015, he was part of a series of portraits of the trans community published in [[The New Yorker|The New Yorker.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/photo-booth/transgender-portraits-and-the-things-a-body-wont-tell|title=Transgender Portraits and the Things a Body Won\u2019t Tell|last=Weinstein|first=Michael M.|website=The New Yorker|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> He shared his reflections and wisdom for trans youth in a [[BuzzFeed]] article<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/skarlan/you-are-loved|title=What Trans Youth Need To Hear Right Now, According To Trans Adults|last=Karlan|first=Sarah|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and his discussion of what it's like to wear a chest binder was part of a [[BuzzFeed]] short film.<ref>{{Citation|title=BuzzFeed LGBTQ on Facebook Watch|url=https://www.facebook.com/BuzzFeedLGBTQ/videos/what-its-like-to-wear-a-chest-binder/844538515673335/|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> In 2016, he advocated to increase accessibility to [[gender affirmation surgery]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/53g5aq/the-organization-that-wants-to-make-gender-affirmation-surgery-easier|title=The Organization That Wants to Make Gender Affirmation Surgery Easier|last=Hope|first=Allison|date=2016-12-09|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His transition and personal journey towards self acceptance was portrayed in an online [[BBC]] video series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/magazine-34884494/trans-man-learning-to-love-my-body|title=Trans man: 'Learning to love my body'|website=BBC News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nZosherafatain was born in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], the oldest of two. He was assigned female at birth and born to an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] father and a [[Greeks|Greek]] mother. His father is originally from [[Tehran]], [[Iran]] and his mother is from [[Ganochora]], [[Greece]]. Due to the [[Iranian Revolution]], his father had to escape from Iran, and his mother left a farming village in [[Greece]] in search of a better life. He has a younger sibling named [[Aristotle|Aristotle.]] Both siblings are first-generation Americans. He spent most of his life in [[Reading, Massachusetts]], and played ice hockey as his main sport. In middle school, he would frequently borrow his family's [[camcorder]] to film his neighborhood friends playing pranks.\n\nAfter spending one year at [[Reading Memorial High School]], he transferred to [[Tabor Academy (Massachusetts)]] as a sophomore. After graduating with honors from Tabor, he was accepted to [[Wesleyan University]] where he pursued student government, film making, activism, and writing. He was a [[Watson Fellow]] finalist in his senior year at Wesleyan for his proposal to produce a documentary about transgender identity across diverse cultural settings. Upon his graduation from Wesleyan in 2010, he went on to attend [[New York University]] and moved to [[New York City]] to begin his film career.\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Short films ===\n* ''Fratello'' (2019)\n* ''Venture Out'' (2020)\n\n=== Short documentaries ===\n* ''I am Isak'' (2017)\n* ''Call me Kye'' (2019)\n* ''Finding Cedar'' (2020)\n\n=== Feature documentaries ===\n* ''Trans in Trumpland'' (2020)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zosherafatain, Tony}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "'''Tony Zosherafatain''' (born December 21, 1987) is an American [[Film director|director]], producer, and [[writer]] from [[Boston|Boston, Massachusetts]]. He openly identifies as a [[transgender]] man and has directed and produced award-winning films about trans identity. As a documentarian, his films utilize a character-driven lens to portray [[Transidentity|trans identity]], [[intersectionality]], [[civil and political rights]], and [[political movements]]. He is the current [[Film director|Director]] of ''[https://www.transintrumpland.com/ Trans in Trumpland,]'' a forthcoming documentary about the [[Trump (president)|Trump]] administration's impact on transgender [[Americans]]. The film is produced through [https://www.transwavefilms.com TransWave Films], a production company run by Zosherafatain and fellow trans filmmaker Jamie DiNicola, and is supported by Executive Producer [[Miss Major Griffin-Gracy]]. [[Jason B. Kohl]] serves as Lead Editor of ''Trans in Trumpland'' alongside [[Tchavdar Georgiev]] as Consulting Editor. After a successful [[Kickstarter]] campaign<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/transintrumpland/trans-in-trumpland/description|title=Trans in Trumpland Kickstarter|last=|first=|date=|website=Kickstarter|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and media coverage by [[GLAAD]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glaad.org/blog/glaad-wrap-trailers-now-apocalypse-and-billions-critics-choice-award-winners-and-more|title=The GLAAD Wrap: Trailers for 'Now Apocalypse' and 'Billions,' Critics' Choice Award winners, and more!|date=2019-01-17|website=GLAAD|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, the film completed production in 2019 and is in post-production.<ref>{{Citation|title=Trans in Trumpland|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt9163946/|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nTony began his film career in 2012 after realizing that there weren't many films about transgender stories.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm8697282/|title=Tony Zosherafatain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> His current and prior films include ''[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt12079070/?ref_=nm_knf_t1 Finding Cedar,] [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11056716/?ref_=nm_knf_t4 Fratello], [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6407488/?ref_=nm_knf_t3 I am Isak,] and [https://www.transwavefilms.com/venture-out Venture Out]''. Venture Out was selected for distribution by [[Recreational Equipment, Inc.|REI]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rei.com/blog/hike/rei-presents-venture-out|title=REI Presents: Venture Out|last=Staff|first=R. E. I.|date=2020-02-20|website=REI Co-op Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His films have screened at domestic and international [[Film festival|film festivals,]] including [[Inside Out Film and Video Festival|Inside Out]], [https://www.theemerginglens.com Emerging Lens], Thessaloniki LGBT Film Festival<ref>{{Citation|title=I am Isak|url=https://www.filmfestival.gr/en/movie/movie/7546|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, and [[Shanghai Queer Film Festival]]. He was the recipient of a Finalist Award at Emerging Lens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theemerginglens.com/awards|title=2017 AWARD WINNERS...|website=emerginglens|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nHis writing blends his identity background, personal anecdotes, and commentary on societal issues to reflect on modern [[American society]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Nixon|first=Paul G.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NR0xDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT109&lpg=PT109&dq=tony+zosherafatain+writer&source=bl&ots=qaYbEi2c1m&sig=ACfU3U1sWpkoRaeFCvVAF6WIilPXZR7wpg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj1sMalpu7oAhVUhHIEHSLxAog4ChDoATABegQICxAo#v=onepage&q=tony%20zosherafatain%20writer&f=false|title=Sex in the Digital Age|last2=D\u00fcsterh\u00f6ft|first2=Isabel K.|date=2017-08-16|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-315-44622-6|language=en}}</ref> He began writing for the [[HuffPost|Huffington Post]] in 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/author/anthony-zosherafatain|title=Tony Zosherafatain {{!}} HuffPost|website=www.huffpost.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> after realizing he faced unique challenges as a transgender [[Iranian Americans|Iranian-American.]] After releasing an article entitled \"I\u2019m Iranian-American. This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like\", his writing was published on the [[HuffPost|Huffington Post]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/im-iranian-american-this-is-what-trumps-america_b_58a49fb3e4b0cd37efcfefd5|title=I'm Iranian-American. This Is What Trump's America Feels Like.|last=Zosherafatain|first=Tony|last2=filmmaker|first2=ContributorI'm a|date=2017-02-15|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16|last3=Writer|first3=A.|last4=Immigrants|first4=The Son of|last5=Person|first5=A. Progress-Minded}}</ref>, [[Thought Catalog]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/tony-zosherafatain/2017/03/im-iranian-american-and-this-is-what-trumps-america-feels-like-to-me/|title=I\u2019m Iranian-American And This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like To Me|date=2017-03-28|website=Thought Catalog|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and [[Medium (website)|Medium.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.politicsmeanspolitics.com/im-iranian-american-this-is-what-trump-s-america-feels-like-7345e666b6b8|title=I\u2019m Iranian-American. This Is What Trump\u2019s America Feels Like.|last=Zosherafatain|first=Tony|date=2017-02-20|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> He appeared in [[Mark Seliger]]'s book ''[https://www.rizzoliusa.com/book/9780847858316/ On Christopher Street: Transgender Stories]'' and was featured in the [[The New York Times|New York Times]]<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bernstein|first=Jacob|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/29/style/transgender-christopher-street-photography-book-mark-seliger.html|title=A Trans Life, Captured by Mark Seliger|date=2016-09-28|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and [[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate (LGBT magazine).]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/books/2016/10/04/transgender-stories-christopher-street-photos|title=Transgender Stories on Christopher Street (Photos)|date=2016-10-04|website=www.advocate.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> In 2015, he was part of a series of portraits of the trans community published in [[The New Yorker|The New Yorker.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/photo-booth/transgender-portraits-and-the-things-a-body-wont-tell|title=Transgender Portraits and the Things a Body Won\u2019t Tell|last=Weinstein|first=Michael M.|website=The New Yorker|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> He shared his reflections and wisdom for trans youth in a [[BuzzFeed]] article<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/skarlan/you-are-loved|title=What Trans Youth Need To Hear Right Now, According To Trans Adults|last=Karlan|first=Sarah|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and his discussion of what it's like to wear a chest binder appeared in a [[BuzzFeed]] short film.<ref>{{Citation|title=BuzzFeed LGBTQ on Facebook Watch|url=https://www.facebook.com/BuzzFeedLGBTQ/videos/what-its-like-to-wear-a-chest-binder/844538515673335/|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> In 2016, he advocated to increase accessibility to [[gender affirmation surgery]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/53g5aq/the-organization-that-wants-to-make-gender-affirmation-surgery-easier|title=The Organization That Wants to Make Gender Affirmation Surgery Easier|last=Hope|first=Allison|date=2016-12-09|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His transition and personal journey towards self acceptance was portrayed in an online [[BBC]] video series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/magazine-34884494/trans-man-learning-to-love-my-body|title=Trans man: 'Learning to love my body'|website=BBC News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nZosherafatain was born in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], the oldest of two. He was assigned female at birth and born to an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] father and a [[Greeks|Greek]] mother. His father is originally from [[Tehran]], [[Iran]] and his mother is from [[Ganochora]], [[Greece]]. Due to the [[Iranian Revolution]], his father had to escape from Iran, and his mother left a farming village in [[Greece]] in search of a better life. He has a younger sibling named [[Aristotle|Aristotle.]] Both siblings are first-generation Americans. He spent most of his life in [[Reading, Massachusetts]], and played ice hockey as his main sport. In middle school, he would frequently borrow his family's [[camcorder]] to film his neighborhood friends playing pranks.\n\nAfter spending one year at [[Reading Memorial High School]], he transferred to [[Tabor Academy (Massachusetts)]] as a sophomore. After graduating with honors from Tabor, he was accepted to [[Wesleyan University]] where he pursued student government, film making, activism, and writing. He was a [[Watson Fellow]] finalist in his senior year at Wesleyan for his proposal to produce a documentary about transgender identity across diverse cultural settings. Upon his graduation from Wesleyan in 2010, he went on to attend [[New York University]] and moved to [[New York City]] to begin his film career.\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Short films ===\n* ''Fratello'' (2019)\n* ''Venture Out'' (2020)\n\n=== Short documentaries ===\n* ''I am Isak'' (2017)\n* ''Call me Kye'' (2019)\n* ''Finding Cedar'' (2020)\n\n=== Feature documentaries ===\n* ''Trans in Trumpland'' (2020)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zosherafatain, Tony}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "JDassistant", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Zosherafatain"}
{"title_page": "TV Derana", "text_new": "{{Infobox television channel\n| name              =  Derana TV( BORU TV)\n| logofile          = Logo TV Derana.jpg\n| logosize          = \n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| logo2             = \n| established       = \n| airdate           = \n| launch            = {{Date|11 October 2005 |dmy deranafv}}\n| closed date       = \n| picture format    =\n| share             = \n| share as of       = \n| share source      = \n| network           = \n| owner             =  Power House LTD \n| parent            = \nPicture Format      = ([[576i]], [[SDTV]])|\n| key people        = Dilith Jayaweera\n| slogan            = \"\u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0daf\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1, \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\"<br>\n\"Ape De Rekagena, Aluth De Aragena\"\n| motto             =\n| country           = [[Sri Lanka]]\n| language          = [[Sinhalese language|Sinhalese]]\n| broadcast area    = Sri Lanka\n| affiliates        =\n| headquarters _,  , No 699\n\nColombo\n| former names      =\n| replaced names    = \n| replaced by names = \n| sister names      = {{Ubl|[[Ada Derana|Ada Derana 24\u00d77]]|[[FM Derana]]}}\n| timeshift names   = \n| web               = {{url|www.derana.lk}} \n| terr serv 1       = [[UHF]] ([[Colombo]])\n| terr chan 1       = Channel 37<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/051009/tv/5.html |title=\u2018Derana\u2019 is born |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref>\n| terr serv 2       = [[UHF]] ([[Kandy]])\n| terr chan 2       = Channel 32\n| terr serv 3       = [[UHF]] ([[Nayabedda]])\n| terr chan 3       = Channel 32\n| terr serv 4       = [[UHF]] ([[Badulla]])\n| terr chan 4       = Channel 31\n| terr serv 5       = [[UHF]] ([[Gongala]])\n| terr chan 5       = Channel 31\n| terr serv 6       = [[UHF]] ([[Ratnapura]])\n| terr chan 6       = Channel 30\n| terr serv 7       = [[UHF]] ([[Nuwara Eliya]])\n| terr chan 7       = Channel 36\n| terr serv 8       =[[UHF]]\n([[Kalutara]])\n| terr chan 8       = Channel 56\n| terr serv 10      = TV Lanka Digital TV \n| terr chan 10      = Channel 5\n| sat serv 1        = [[Dialog TV]]\n| sat chan 1        = Channel 6\n| sat serv 2        = [[Dish TV Sri Lanka]]\n| sat chan 2        = Channel 2514\n| cable serv 1      = [[Ask Cable Vision]]\n| cable chan 1      = Channel 8\n| iptv serv 1       = [[PEO TV]]\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 4\n| online serv 1     =\n}}\n\n'''TV Derana''' is a [[Sinhalese language]] state run [[entertainment]] [[ terrestrial television]] channel broadcasting in [[Sri Lanka]]. Launched on 11 October 2005,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/051002/tv/3.html |title=\u2018Derana\u2019: A new TV Channel for Lankan family audiences |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref> it is one of the most popular television networks in the country.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} Its main transmission tower is on the [[Kikilimana]] mountain, and coverage is extended nationwide via eight transmission towers. It is the second television channel to offer REAL TIME web casting of daily programmes in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/060101/tv/8.html | title=Real Time on Derana | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe channel is available on digital medium through [[Dialog TV]], [[PEO TV]] and the newly launched OTT platform GLUUOO. Derana broadcasts contemporary content that upholds Sri Lankan values on its \"\u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0daf\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1, \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\" / \u201cApe De Rakagena, Aluth De Aragena\u201d (Conserve our own and embrace the new) platforms.\n\nThe channel focuses heavily on high-end programming that meets stringent expectations of viewers in the two premium socio-economic categorizations SEC A and SEC B. Currently TV Derana is the No. 1 television channel in Sri Lanka, according to late 2017 LMRB search data.<ref>http://www.lmrbint.com</ref> The channel has maintained this position since March 2017. TV Derana also holds the all-time record for having the most number of programmes by one channel, in the top 10 most rated programmes. According to the recent LMRB research data, TV Derana has eight programmes in the top 10 including the first two programmes in the country..<ref>[http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=35887 \"Derena celebrates sixth anniversary\"], The Island Online, 1 October 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.adaderana.lk/news/39554/tv-derana-ranked-sri-lankas-no-1-tv-channel], \"TV Derana ranked Sri Lanka\u2019s No. 1 TV channel\"</ref>\n\n==Programming==\nThe channel broadcasts a range of entertainment programmes including [[Soap opera|dramas]], [[reality shows]], [[kids programme]]s, music and [[variety shows]]. It operates 16 hours a day, between 05:00 and 24:00.<ref>[http://www.derana.lk/index.php?route=schedule/schedule/schedule&dt=2012-1-16 Derana TV Program Schedule]</ref>\n\n===Current shows===\n{{prose|section|date=May 2016}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Drama====\n*[[Sidu (Malee 3)]]\n*[[Deveni Inima]]\n*[[Muthu Kuda]]\n*[[Muthulendora]]\n*Nataka Marayi Navaya Hamarayi\n*Kanthoru Moru\n*[[Ravana|Ravana (2018 TV Series)]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.derana.lk/Ravana-Teledrama&vid=21840&page=1}}</ref>\n*[[Kusumasana Devi]]\n*[[Sangeethe]]\n*[[Heyli]]\n\n====Dubbed programmes====\n*[[:pt:Escola de G%C3%AAnios|Amuthu Iskole (Escola de G\u00eanios)]]\n*[[Wizards vs Aliens|Maya Sakwala]]\n*[[Meri Durga|Duwana Lamaya]]\n*[[Meri Aashiqui Tum Se Hi|Sadahatama Oba Mage]]\n*[[Bandhan (TV series)|Ali Malliy Mamai]] (Re-run)\n*[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat|Adiraja Dharmashoka]]\n*[[H2O: Just Add Water|Kinduru Kumariyo]]\n*[[Wolfblood|Wurka Shapaya]] or as [[Wolfblood|Puduma Yaluwo]]\n*[[Mako: Island of Secrets|Kinduru Kumara]]\n*[[Beyhadh|Obath Mamath Ayath]]\n*[[Bhutu|Chuti Du]]\n*[[K\u0131rg\u0131n \u00c7i\u00e7ekler|Muthu Ahura]]<ref>[[:tr:K%C4%B1rg%C4%B1n %C3%87i%C3%A7ekler|Orphan Flowers]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=May 2018}}\n*[[Prithvi Vallabh - Itihaas Bhi, Rahasya Bhi|Pruthivi Maharaja]]\n*[[Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala|Mini Pahana Obai]]\n*[[Koinaka|Best Friends in Love]]\n*[[Bepannah|Hamuwemu Aye Sansare]]\n*[[Tenali Rama (TV series)|Panditha Rama]]\n*[[Every Witch Way|Magic Lamai]]\n*[[Boys Over Flowers (TV series)|Boys Over Flowers]]\n*[[The Heirs]]\n\n====Music====\n*Music Online\n*Dell Studio\n*Maa Nowana Mama\n*Sindu Kamare\n*Singhagiri Studio\n*Leya Saha laya\n*Cassette Eka\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n====News====\n*Mid Day News Bulletin\n*Biz Journal\n*Ada Derana (6.55p.m.)\n*Ada Derana (10p.m.)\n\n====Reality====\n*Derana City of Dance\n*Derana Little Star\n*Derana Miss Sri Lanka\n*Derana Dream Star \n*[[Derana Film Awards]]\n*Derana Star City \n*Derana 60 plus\n*Derana Music Video Awards<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/101114/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_5.html |title=Vibrant new generation music |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=29 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Talk shows====\n*360\u00b0\n*Wada Pitiya\n*Aluth Parlimenthuwa\n*No Politics\n*Mihiri Mathaka Magul Gedera\n*Awakashaya\n*Mata Mathaka Widihata\n*Malbara Derana\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Variety====\n*Fengshui\n*Baiscope\n*Bahujana Hithaya\n*Paara Kiyana Tharuka\n*Sinhala Movie\n*Patta Pata Pata\n*Mehemath Samayan\n*Breakfast to Dinner\n*Lanka Soy Game Show\n*Pita Pita Baadhaka\n*Onna Ottui\n*Ammai Mamai\n*Seda Mawatha\n*Mangala Shihina\n*Baiscope\n*Dream Star Chart Show\n*Travel With Chathura\n*Malbara Derana\n*Thathvika\n*Belimal With Peshala & Denuwan\n*Dishum Dishum\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n====Kids programmes====\n*Tring Tring Show\n*School TV\n*Kids Movies\n*Badagini Time\n*Noddy\n*Vidya Pavula\n\n====Bridal programme====\n*Vivaha\n*Mangala Sihina\n\n====Cartoons====\n[[Tiny Toon Adventures|Tiny Toon Adventures (2008-2011)]]\n\n\n*Chuttai Chuttiyi\n*[[Motu Patlu|Sootin Martin]]\n*Inspector Pretty\n*Allan Sellam\n*Raja Kesbawo\n*Bob & Margret\n*Buddhi and Bunty\n*Walas Mulla\n*Amden or Danga putha\n*[[The Smurfs (TV series)|Nil Kurumitto]]\n*Makara Rajadaniya\n*Nidhan Doopatha\n*No katha More sina\n\n==Ada Derana==\n''Ada Derana'' is a news website operated by Derana. Its content is available in English, Sinhala. and [[Tamil language|Tamil]]. It is ranked as one of the most popular local news websites by [[Alexa Internet|Alexa]].<ref>[http://www.adaderana.lk/ Ada Derana News]</ref><ref>[http://www.alexa.com/topsites/countries/LK Top sites in Sri Lanka], Alexa</ref>\n\nIn late 2007, Ada Derana entered into a partnership with [[Dialog Telekom]], the largest mobile phone operator in Sri Lanka, to send breaking news alerts to all Dialog mobile subscribers as [[SMS|text messages]].<ref>[http://www.telecompaper.com/news/dialog-telekom-launches-derana-news-alert-service \"Dialog Telekom launches Derana news alert service\"], Telecompaper, 13 November 2007</ref> Currently, instant news alerts can be obtained through all the leading mobile phone operators in Sri Lanka.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}\n\n==Ada Derana 24x7==\n[[Ada Derana|Ada Derana 24x7]] is Sri Lanka\u2019s first ever 24-hour television news channel and first dedicated news channel.\n[[Ada Derana|More about Ada Derana]]\n\n==Competitions and sponsorship==\nDerana has hosted the [[Miss World]] Miss Sri Lanka pageant since 2007.<ref>[http://derana.lk/misssrilanka/about.php Derana Veet Miss Sri Lanka]</ref>\n\nDerana has conducted the ''Derana London Star'' since May 2008 in London, UK, to find the most talented upcoming singer among the Sri Lankans living in UK. The first edition received around 220 applications, and auditions were broadcast in Sri Lanka by Derana TV.<ref>[http://www.ovguide.com/derana-london-star-9202a8c04000641f800000000f176443# Derana London Star]</ref> The winners were determined by a panel of judges and public votes via SMS.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}\n\nTV Derana is the first channel that hosted a reality show for children in Sri Lanka. The first season was named as ''Derana Star in a Minute''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/070429/TV/004tv.html |title=Star in a minute |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref> and the rest of the seasons as ''Derana Little Star''.<ref>http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/01/28/?fn=sa16012829</ref><ref>http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/02/04/?fn=sa16020415</ref> Up to date, six seasons of ''Little Star'' were finished and the seventh season will start soon.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/Little-Star-Season-07-TV-Derana</ref>\n\nDerana started a dancing reality competition with the name ''Derana City of Dance''. Five seasons are finished in the show.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/index.php?route=programs/programs/programdetails&pid=192</ref>\n\nThe most popular of all reality shows of Derana is ''Derana Dream Star'', and seven seasons finished and the eighth season is about to start.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/dreamstar/</ref> It started in 2009.\n\n===''Derana Dream Star''===\n''Derana Dream Star'' is a music reality show produced by Derana TV. It started in 2009 and now it had successfully completed seven seasons.\n\n====Season I (2009)====\n# Udesh Indula (Winner)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/090125/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_02.html | title=Udesh hits the highest note | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n# Milinda Sandaruwan (Runner Up)\n\n====Season II (2010)====\n# Upekha Nirmani (Winner)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/100502/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_11.html |title=Upekha Nirmani is Derana Dream Star |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n# Udesh Manoj (Runner Up)\n\n# \n# \n\n# \n# \n\n# \n# \n\n# \n# \n\n# \n# \n\n# \n# \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.derana.lk Official Website]\n* [http://www.adaderana.lk/ Ada Derana]\n\n{{Media of Sri Lanka}}\n\n[[Category:Power House]]\n[[Category:Sinhala-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Media in Colombo]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2005]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television channel\n| name              =  Derana TV( BORU TV)\n| logofile          = Logo TV Derana.jpg\n| logosize          = \n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| logo2             = \n| established       = \n| airdate           = \n| launch            = {{Date|11 October 2005 |dmy deranafv}}\n| closed date       = \n| picture format    =\n| share             = \n| share as of       = \n| share source      = \n| network           = \n| owner             =  Power House LTD \n| parent            = \nPicture Format      = ([[576i]], [[SDTV]])|\n| key people        = Dilith Jayaweera\n| slogan            = \"\u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0daf\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1, \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\"<br>\n\"Ape De Rekagena, Aluth De Aragena\"\n| motto             =\n| country           = [[Sri Lanka]]\n| language          = [[Sinhalese language|Sinhalese]]\n| broadcast area    = Sri Lanka\n| affiliates        =\n| headquarters _,  , No 699\n\nColombo\n| former names      =\n| replaced names    = \n| replaced by names = \n| sister names      = {{Ubl|[[Ada Derana|Ada Derana 24\u00d77]]|[[FM Derana]]}}\n| timeshift names   = \n| web               = {{url|www.derana.lk}} \n| terr serv 1       = [[UHF]] ([[Colombo]])\n| terr chan 1       = Channel 37<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/051009/tv/5.html |title=\u2018Derana\u2019 is born |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref>\n| terr serv 2       = [[UHF]] ([[Kandy]])\n| terr chan 2       = Channel 32\n| terr serv 3       = [[UHF]] ([[Nayabedda]])\n| terr chan 3       = Channel 32\n| terr serv 4       = [[UHF]] ([[Badulla]])\n| terr chan 4       = Channel 31\n| terr serv 5       = [[UHF]] ([[Gongala]])\n| terr chan 5       = Channel 31\n| terr serv 6       = [[UHF]] ([[Ratnapura]])\n| terr chan 6       = Channel 30\n| terr serv 7       = [[UHF]] ([[Nuwara Eliya]])\n| terr chan 7       = Channel 36\n| terr serv 8       =[[UHF]]\n([[Kalutara]])\n| terr chan 8       = Channel 56\n| terr serv 10      = TV Lanka Digital TV \n| terr chan 10      = Channel 5\n| sat serv 1        = [[Dialog TV]]\n| sat chan 1        = Channel 6\n| sat serv 2        = [[Dish TV Sri Lanka]]\n| sat chan 2        = Channel 2514\n| cable serv 1      = [[Ask Cable Vision]]\n| cable chan 1      = Channel 8\n| iptv serv 1       = [[PEO TV]]\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 4\n| online serv 1     =\n}}\n\n'''TV Derana''' is a [[Sinhalese language]] state run [[entertainment]] [[ terrestrial television]] channel broadcasting in [[Sri Lanka]]. Launched on 11 October 2005,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/051002/tv/3.html |title=\u2018Derana\u2019: A new TV Channel for Lankan family audiences |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref> it is one of the most popular television networks in the country.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} Its main transmission tower is on the [[Kikilimana]] mountain, and coverage is extended nationwide via eight transmission towers. It is the second television channel to offer REAL TIME web casting of daily programmes in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/060101/tv/8.html | title=Real Time on Derana | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=18 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe channel is available on digital medium through [[Dialog TV]], [[PEO TV]] and the newly launched OTT platform GLUUOO. Derana broadcasts contemporary content that upholds Sri Lankan values on its \"\u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0daf\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1, \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\" / \u201cApe De Rakagena, Aluth De Aragena\u201d (Conserve our own and embrace the new) platforms.\n\nThe channel focuses heavily on high-end programming that meets stringent expectations of viewers in the two premium socio-economic categorizations SEC A and SEC B. Currently TV Derana is the No. 1 television channel in Sri Lanka, according to late 2017 LMRB search data.<ref>http://www.lmrbint.com</ref> The channel has maintained this position since March 2017. TV Derana also holds the all-time record for having the most number of programmes by one channel, in the top 10 most rated programmes. According to the recent LMRB research data, TV Derana has eight programmes in the top 10 including the first two programmes in the country..<ref>[http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=35887 \"Derena celebrates sixth anniversary\"], The Island Online, 1 October 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.adaderana.lk/news/39554/tv-derana-ranked-sri-lankas-no-1-tv-channel], \"TV Derana ranked Sri Lanka\u2019s No. 1 TV channel\"</ref>\n\n==Programming==\nThe channel broadcasts a range of entertainment programmes including [[Soap opera|dramas]], [[reality shows]], [[kids programme]]s, music and [[variety shows]]. It operates 16 hours a day, between 05:00 and 24:00.<ref>[http://www.derana.lk/index.php?route=schedule/schedule/schedule&dt=2012-1-16 Derana TV Program Schedule]</ref>\n\n===Current shows===\n{{prose|section|date=May 2016}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Drama====\n*[[Sidu (Malee 3)]]\n*[[Deveni Inima]]\n*[[Muthu Kuda]]\n*[[Muthulendora]]\n*Nataka Marayi Navaya Hamarayi\n*Kanthoru Moru\n*[[Ravana|Ravana (2018 TV Series)]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.derana.lk/Ravana-Teledrama&vid=21840&page=1}}</ref>\n*[[Kusumasana Devi]]\n*[[Sangeethe]]\n*[[Heyli]]\n\n====Dubbed programmes====\n*[[:pt:Escola de G%C3%AAnios|Amuthu Iskole (Escola de G\u00eanios)]]\n*[[Wizards vs Aliens|Maya Sakwala]]\n*[[Meri Durga|Duwana Lamaya]]\n*[[Meri Aashiqui Tum Se Hi|Sadahatama Oba Mage]]\n*[[Bandhan (TV series)|Ali Malliy Mamai]] (Re-run)\n*[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat|Adiraja Dharmashoka]]\n*[[H2O: Just Add Water|Kinduru Kumariyo]]\n*[[Wolfblood|Wurka Shapaya]] or as [[Wolfblood|Puduma Yaluwo]]\n*[[Mako: Island of Secrets|Kinduru Kumara]]\n*[[Beyhadh|Obath Mamath Ayath]]\n*[[Bhutu|Chuti Du]]\n*[[K\u0131rg\u0131n \u00c7i\u00e7ekler|Muthu Ahura]]<ref>[[:tr:K%C4%B1rg%C4%B1n %C3%87i%C3%A7ekler|Orphan Flowers]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=May 2018}}\n*[[Prithvi Vallabh - Itihaas Bhi, Rahasya Bhi|Pruthivi Maharaja]]\n*[[Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala|Mini Pahana Obai]]\n*[[Koinaka|Best Friends in Love]]\n*[[Bepannah|Hamuwemu Aye Sansare]]\n*[[Tenali Rama (TV series)|Panditha Rama]]\n*[[Every Witch Way|Magic Lamai]]\n*[[Boys Over Flowers (TV series)|Boys Over Flowers]]\n*[[The Heirs]]\n\n====Music====\n*Music Online\n*Dell Studio\n*Maa Nowana Mama\n*Sindu Kamare\n*Singhagiri Studio\n*Leya Saha laya\n*Cassette Eka\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n====News====\n*Mid Day News Bulletin\n*Biz Journal\n*Ada Derana (6.55p.m.)\n*Ada Derana (10p.m.)\n\n====Reality====\n*Derana City of Dance\n*Derana Little Star\n*Derana Miss Sri Lanka\n*Derana Dream Star \n*[[Derana Film Awards]]\n*Derana Star City \n*Derana 60 plus\n*Derana Music Video Awards<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/101114/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_5.html |title=Vibrant new generation music |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=29 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Talk shows====\n*360\u00b0\n*Wada Pitiya\n*Aluth Parlimenthuwa\n*No Politics\n*Mihiri Mathaka Magul Gedera\n*Awakashaya\n*Mata Mathaka Widihata\n*Malbara Derana\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Variety====\n*Fengshui\n*Baiscope\n*Bahujana Hithaya\n*Paara Kiyana Tharuka\n*Sinhala Movie\n*Patta Pata Pata\n*Mehemath Samayan\n*Breakfast to Dinner\n*Lanka Soy Game Show\n*Pita Pita Baadhaka\n*Onna Ottui\n*Ammai Mamai\n*Seda Mawatha\n*Mangala Shihina\n*Baiscope\n*Dream Star Chart Show\n*Travel With Chathura\n*Malbara Derana\n*Thathvika\n*Belimal With Peshala & Denuwan\n*Dishum Dishum\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n====Kids programmes====\n*Tring Tring Show\n*School TV\n*Kids Movies\n*Badagini Time\n*Noddy\n*Vidya Pavula\n\n====Bridal programme====\n*Vivaha\n*Mangala Sihina\n\n====Cartoons====\n[[Tiny Toon Adventures|Tiny Toon Adventures (2008-2011)]]\n\n\n*Chuttai Chuttiyi\n*[[Motu Patlu|Sootin Martin]]\n*Inspector Pretty\n*Allan Sellam\n*Raja Kesbawo\n*Bob & Margret\n*Buddhi and Bunty\n*Walas Mulla\n*Amden or Danga putha\n*[[The Smurfs (TV series)|Nil Kurumitto]]\n*Makara Rajadaniya\n*Nidhan Doopatha\n*No katha More sina\n\n==Ada Derana==\n''Ada Derana'' is a news website operated by Derana. Its content is available in English, Sinhala. and [[Tamil language|Tamil]]. It is ranked as one of the most popular local news websites by [[Alexa Internet|Alexa]].<ref>[http://www.adaderana.lk/ Ada Derana News]</ref><ref>[http://www.alexa.com/topsites/countries/LK Top sites in Sri Lanka], Alexa</ref>\n\nIn late 2007, Ada Derana entered into a partnership with [[Dialog Telekom]], the largest mobile phone operator in Sri Lanka, to send breaking news alerts to all Dialog mobile subscribers as [[SMS|text messages]].<ref>[http://www.telecompaper.com/news/dialog-telekom-launches-derana-news-alert-service \"Dialog Telekom launches Derana news alert service\"], Telecompaper, 13 November 2007</ref> Currently, instant news alerts can be obtained through all the leading mobile phone operators in Sri Lanka.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}\n\n==Ada Derana 24x7==\n[[Ada Derana|Ada Derana 24x7]] is Sri Lanka\u2019s first ever 24-hour television news channel and first dedicated news channel.\n[[Ada Derana|More about Ada Derana]]\n\n==Competitions and sponsorship==\nDerana has hosted the [[Miss World]] Miss Sri Lanka pageant since 2007.<ref>[http://derana.lk/misssrilanka/about.php Derana Veet Miss Sri Lanka]</ref>\n\nDerana has conducted the ''Derana London Star'' since May 2008 in London, UK, to find the most talented upcoming singer among the Sri Lankans living in UK. The first edition received around 220 applications, and auditions were broadcast in Sri Lanka by Derana TV.<ref>[http://www.ovguide.com/derana-london-star-9202a8c04000641f800000000f176443# Derana London Star]</ref> The winners were determined by a panel of judges and public votes via SMS.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}\n\nTV Derana is the first channel that hosted a reality show for children in Sri Lanka. The first season was named as ''Derana Star in a Minute''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/070429/TV/004tv.html |title=Star in a minute |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref> and the rest of the seasons as ''Derana Little Star''.<ref>http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/01/28/?fn=sa16012829</ref><ref>http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/02/04/?fn=sa16020415</ref> Up to date, six seasons of ''Little Star'' were finished and the seventh season will start soon.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/Little-Star-Season-07-TV-Derana</ref>\n\nDerana started a dancing reality competition with the name ''Derana City of Dance''. Five seasons are finished in the show.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/index.php?route=programs/programs/programdetails&pid=192</ref>\n\nThe most popular of all reality shows of Derana is ''Derana Dream Star'', and seven seasons finished and the eighth season is about to start.<ref>http://www.derana.lk/dreamstar/</ref> It started in 2009.\n\n===''Derana Dream Star''===\n''Derana Dream Star'' is a music reality show produced by Derana TV. It started in 2009 and now it had successfully completed seven seasons.\n\n====Season I (2009)====\n# Udesh Indula (Winner)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/090125/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_02.html | title=Udesh hits the highest note | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n# Milinda Sandaruwan (Runner Up)\n\n====Season II (2010)====\n# Upekha Nirmani (Winner)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/100502/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_11.html |title=Upekha Nirmani is Derana Dream Star |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n# Udesh Manoj (Runner Up)\n\n====Season III (2011)====\n# Keshan Shashindra (Winner)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2011/08/04/_art.asp?fn=sa11080419&pn=20 |title=Dream Star season 3 grand finale |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>\n# Shanaka Udeesha (Runner Up)\n\n====Season IV (2012)====\n# Sasindu Wijesiri (Winner)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2012/12/13/?fn=sa1212139 |title=\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dab \u0da9\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca 04 |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>\n# Raween Kanishka (Runner Up)\n\n====Season V (2014)====\n# M.G Danushka (Winner)\n# Vishmitha Sachintha (Runner Up)\n\n====Season VI (2015)====\n# Janith Iddamalgoda<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2015/12/10/?fn=sa15121026 |title=Most girls love this hair cut |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref> (Winner)\n# Yashodha Priyadarshani (Runner Up)\n\n====Season VII (2017)====\n# Suneera Sumanga<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2017/12/14/?fn=sa17121423 |title=Derana Dream Star season 7 winner |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=17 December 2017}}</ref> (Winner)\n# Shalin Kaushalya (Runner Up)\n\n====Season VIII (2018)====\n# Thanura Madugeeth<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adaderana.lk/entertainment/53695/thanura-madugeeth-wins-derana-dream-star-season-8 |title=Derana Dream Star season 8 winner |publisher=Ada Derana |accessdate=10 March 2019}}</ref> (Winner)\n# Raveen Tharuka (Runner Up)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.derana.lk Official Website]\n* [http://www.adaderana.lk/ Ada Derana]\n\n{{Media of Sri Lanka}}\n\n[[Category:Power House]]\n[[Category:Sinhala-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Media in Colombo]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2005]]\n", "name_user": "112.134.74.154", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Derana TV)",